ue critical intervention into our understanding of queer Irish cultures in the wake of the 2015 referendum and the Varadkar election.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish fictionxIrish authorsy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish fictionxIrish authorsy21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGay men in literature. 0aMale homosexuality in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Modern / 20th Century .2bisacsh  aBrendan Behan.  aIrish fiction.  aJohn Broderick.  aLGBT politics.  acolm toibin.  acoming out romance.  ahistorical romance.  aidentity politics.  apolitics.  areformism.1 aCronin, Michael G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613543840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526135438423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526135438/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles